Schneiderman, New York\u2019s attorney general, is said to be conducting a broad investigation into whether banks are deliberately choking off mortgage lending to predominantly minority communities, known as \u201credlining,\u201d DealBook\u2019s Jessica Silver-Greenberg writes. {"abstract": "Cutting costs and eliminating huge legal bills have helped the bank, but its rivals are ahead on efficiency, among other areas.", "web_url": "https://www.nytimes.com/2015/10/15/business/dealbook/bank-of-americas-hunt-for-growth.html", "snippet": "Cutting costs and eliminating huge legal bills have helped the bank, but its rivals are ahead on efficiency, among other areas.", "lead_paragraph": "Wells Fargo and JPMorgan have reported third-quarter results that highlight a $7 billion challenge for rival Bank of America. That\u2019s the extra annual profit the lender run by Brian Moynihan would need to earn for a 10 percent return on equity, generally the level at which big banks cover their cost of capital. Cutting spending to match Wells Fargo\u2019s efficient operation would not quite suffice, though.
